                <div class="question" id="question-7">
                    <h3>Question 7</h3>
                    <div class="question-content">
                        <p>Distinguish between discrete and continuous data as used in statistics.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="answer-section">
                        <h4>Answer</h4>
                        <div class="answer-content" id="answer-7">
                            <div class="answer-detail">
                                <p><strong>1. Discrete Data:</strong></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Data that can only take specific, countable values</li>
                                    <li>Has distinct, separate values with clear gaps between them</li>
                                    <li>Cannot be measured to infinite precision</li>
                                    <li>Examples:
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Number of students in a class</li>
                                            <li>Number of computers in a lab</li>
                                            <li>Count of errors in a program</li>
                                            <li>Test scores (whole numbers)</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>

                                <p><strong>2. Continuous Data:</strong></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Data that can take any value within a given range</li>
                                    <li>Can be measured to any degree of precision</li>
                                    <li>No gaps between possible values</li>
                                    <li>Examples:
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Height measurements</li>
                                            <li>Time durations</li>
                                            <li>Temperature readings</li>
                                            <li>Speed measurements</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>

                                <div class="key-differences">
                                    <p><strong>Key Differences:</strong></p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>Discrete data can be counted, continuous data is measured</li>
                                        <li>Discrete data has gaps, continuous data does not</li>
                                        <li>Discrete data has finite precision, continuous data can be infinitely precise</li>
                                        <li>Discrete data is represented by points, continuous data by intervals</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

